# Pomikit product philosophy

**Less decisions. Better interfaces.**  
(Also: Beautiful by default. Smart by design.)

## Goal

Pomikit is the Vue library that asks developers for the **fewest decisions** while shipping premium UI by default.

```vue
<Button>Save</Button>
<Input v-model="email" />
<Card>…</Card>
```

## Design once

```ts
createTheme({ design: 'linear', accent: '#5B5FFF' })
```

Design Kits own colors, radius, shadows, spacing, typography, motion, surfaces. Components only consume tokens — no `if (design === …)` in component code.

## Decision filter (required before any new prop/feature)

> Does this require an extra decision from the developer?

If **yes**, first try: Design Kit / tokens → intent inference → conventional behavior.  
Only then expose a prop — and **only** if it expresses business intent (`confirm`, `href`, `required`, `pending`, `error`, `options`…), never pure aesthetics (`variant`, `tone`, `size`, `radius`…).

Style props may remain as advanced escape hatches but must not appear in Getting Started, playground demos, or primary docs examples.

## Docs & examples

Lead with the minimal API. Storybook “escape hatch” stories are internal only.
